[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["S-amer africa default banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Lago Negro12.jpg"],["thumb"],["Gramado, a city in Brazil's southernmost state, Rio Grande do Sul"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Gramado rótula.jpg"],["thumb"],["right"],["Gramado during the Christmas season"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Gramado"]}," is in the state of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rio Grande do Sul"]]},", in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["South (Brazil)"],["Southern Brazil"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nGramado is a municipality and small touristic town, southeast of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Caxias do Sul"]]}," and east of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Nova Petrópolis"]]}," in the southern Brazilian state of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Rio Grande do Sul"]]},", in the Serra Gaúcha region. Most of the population of Gramado are of German or Italian descent. Gramado is one of the towns along the scenic route known as ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rota Romântica"]},". The town is also part of the scenic Região das Hortênsias route.\n\nGramado hosts the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Festival de Gramado"]},", a major South American film festival and Gramado's most important event. Gramado is also known for hydrangea blossoms in late spring. Another key event in Gramado is ",{"type":"'''","value":["Natal Luz"]},", when Gramado is decked out in lights and wreathes made of recycled material by local residents.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\nGramado is served by two airports: ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hugo Cantergiani Airport"]}," (CXJ) in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Caxias do Sul"]]}," and ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.aeroportoportoalegre.net\/en\/porto-alegre-international-airport-poa Salgado Filho International Airport"]}," (POA) in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Porto Alegre"]]},". There is also an airstrip in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Canela"]]},", which is only used for private airplanes. A plan to create the Hydrangeas Region Airport was halted by a court order due to environmental reasons.\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["CXJ"]},"\n\nHugo Cantergiani Airport",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.st.rs.gov.br\/novosite\/estrutura\/detalhe.php?id=233&idcategoria=9"]}," is a small airport serving Caxias do Sul and, it's some 60km (37mi) away from Gramado. CXJ is basically a collecting airport to ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.aeroportocongonhas.net\/en\/congonhas-airport-cgh Congonhas Airport"]}," in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["São Paulo"]]}," and stopover from flights coming from e to Porto Alegre. Because of that, CXJ tends to be more relaxed on baggage overweight. In general, flights from Congonhas (CGH) to CXJ are cheaper than those flying to POA, an average roundtrip flight CGH-CXJ costs around R$450 (US$210). Infrastructure for visitors is minimal.\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["POA"]},"\n\nSalgado Filho International Airport",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.infraero.gov.br\/aero_prev_home.php?ai=37"]}," is the largest, busiest airport in Rio Grande do Sul and Southern Brazil. POA is some 118km (74mi) away from Gramado. POA has a modern infrastructure, being the first airport in Brazil to have a mall (shopping centre), with movie theaters, food court, shops, duty-free shops, banks and so on. POA is connected to several Brazilian and South American cities.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\nGramado is served by ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.citral.tur.br\/ Citral"]},", which has the franchise to explore bus services in the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Região das Hortênsias"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Vale do Paranhana"]]},". Gramado Bus Station is centrally located, on Borges de Medeiros Avenue, and has a taxi rank.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Igreja Matriz São Pedro.jpg"],["thumb"],["right"],["St. Peter Church"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Lago Negro 2.jpg"],["thumb"],["right"],["Lago Negro (Black Lake) in Gramado"]]},"\nThe area of main touristic interest is along Av. Borges de Medeiros, where sit the St. Peter church, the Festivals Palace, Covered Street, several restaurants, shops and squares.\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Lago Negro"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=surrounded by Araucaria wood that gets full of flowers in summer. Very popular walking spots. Features pedal boats."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Miniworld"],["alt=Mini-mundo"],["url=http:\/\/www.minimundo.com.br\/minimundo\/index.htm"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Outdoors collection of world monuments, such as ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Neuschwanstein"]]}," castle, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Ouro Preto"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Bariloche"]]}," airport, built in 1:24 scale."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Covered Street"],["alt=Rua coberta"],["url="],["email="],["address=city center"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=24h"],["price=Free"],["content=Shopping street with acrylic roof that looks beautiful with Christmas lights."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Parque Knorr"],["url="],["email="],["address=Rua Bela Vista, 353"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Christmas-themed picturesque park, features Santa Claus Grove, Ms. Santa Village, Toy Factory, Wish Tree and Bear Cottage."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Culture Center"],["url="],["email="],["address=Rua São Pedro, 369"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["toll